it didn't cross my mind

5
00:00:08,051 --> 00:00:10,119
that maybe Mike should think
about making a deal.

6
00:00:10,219 --> 00:00:12,273
And now that they've taken in
your father, you can't tell me

7
00:00:12,373 --> 00:00:14,013
that the thought
hasn't crossed yours too.

8
00:00:14,064 --> 00:00:16,605
Thinking about it and talking
about it aren't the same thing.

9
00:00:16,705 --> 00:00:19,823
I got a call about an article
on Mike Ross' meteoric rise

10
00:00:19,875 --> 00:00:21,291
to Junior Partner.

11
00:00:21,327 --> 00:00:23,577
The problem is
there is no Mike Ross.

12
00:00:23,629 --> 00:00:25,162
You reported it
anonymously,

13
00:00:25,214 --> 00:00:26,580
because you didn't want
to look bad.

14
00:00:26,632 --> 00:00:28,382
I reported it anonymously

15
00:00:28,417 --> 00:00:30,584
because I was ashamed
that it happened on my watch.

16
00:00:30,636 --> 00:00:32,753
I loved you, and you let
some stupid secret

17
00:00:32,755 --> 00:00:34,888
come between us because
you couldn't trust me with it.

18
00:00:34,924 --> 00:00:37,391
All you have to do
is admit what you did,

19
00:00:37,426 --> 00:00:38,926
and all of this goes away.

20
00:00:38,928 --> 00:00:40,594
Sheila came forward.

21
00:00:40,646 --> 00:00:42,729
She admitted she was the one
who wrote the e-mail.

22
00:00:42,765 --> 00:00:45,265
You and your partners
are hereby subpoenaed

23
00:00:45,267 --> 00:00:48,735
to hand over every single
document in the entire firm.

24
00:00:52,024 --> 00:00:53,907
Harvey, I'm not sure
this is the best idea.

25
00:00:53,943 --> 00:00:56,577
We need to know what she has.
What's the downside?

26
00:00:56,612 --> 00:00:58,495
The downside is
that we move up the trial.

27
00:00:58,531 --> 00:01:01,415
Mike, this trial's coming,
whether we like it or not.

28
00:01:01,450 --> 00:01:03,617
And the more time we have
knowing her game plan,

29
00:01:03,669 --> 00:01:07,204
the better off we'll be.

30
00:01:07,256 --> 00:01:09,289
Holy shit.
What?

31
00:01:09,291 --> 00:01:11,125
I took the LSATs
with this guy.

32
00:01:11,177 --> 00:01:12,626
So what?

33
00:01:12,628 --> 00:01:15,129
So he can give Gibbs something
she doesn't even have on me yet.

34
00:01:15,131 --> 00:01:17,548
Yes, but to do that, he'd
be ruining his whole career.

35
00:01:17,600 --> 00:01:19,383
Which means, even
if he remembers you,

36
00:01:19,435 --> 00:01:21,051
he's more afraid of you
than you are of him.

37
00:01:21,103 --> 00:01:23,437
So calm the hell down.

38
00:01:23,472 --> 00:01:25,389
All right, let's make
this quick.

39
00:01:25,441 --> 00:01:26,974
Your Honor,
making it quick is exactly

40
00:01:27,026 --> 00:01:28,642
what we're asking you to do.

41
00:01:28,644 --> 00:01:30,477
She hasn't handed over
her discovery yet.

42
00:01:30,479 --> 00:01:32,112
I'm still building a case,

43
00:01:32,148 --> 00:01:33,947
and we haven't even set
a date for the trial yet.

44
00:01:33,983 --> 00:01:35,983
And the check's in the mail,
and all the other things

45
00:01:36,035 --> 00:01:38,535
people say when they don't wanna
do what they have to do.

46
00:01:38,571 --> 00:01:40,091
What I have to do
is protect the public

47
00:01:40,122 --> 00:01:42,002
from the likes of you.
All right, that's enough.

48
00:01:42,041 --> 00:01:43,824
Get that discovery to them
by the end of the day.

49
00:01:43,876 --> 00:01:45,993
In that case, we'd like to ask
that the day of the trial

50
00:01:45,995 --> 00:01:47,544
be set in the next two weeks.

51
00:01:47,580 --> 00:01:49,796
Objection, Your Honor,
she's had weeks to--

52
00:01:49,832 --> 00:01:51,665
You can't have it both ways,
Mr. Specter.

53
00:01:51,667 --> 00:01:54,384
You can't demand discovery
and ask for more time.

54
00:01:54,420 --> 00:01:56,003
Trial starts in two weeks.

55
00:01:59,475 --> 00:02:01,308
Jessica, we have
a problem.

56
00:02:01,343 --> 00:02:02,703
Thanks for pointing
that out, Jack.

57
00:02:02,728 --> 00:02:04,011
I had no idea.

58
00:02:04,063 --> 00:02:05,479
I'm not talking
about the trial.

59
00:02:05,514 --> 00:02:06,847
I'm talking about this.

60
00:02:06,899 --> 00:02:07,981
What the hell is that?

61
00:02:08,017 --> 00:02:10,267
An Op-Ed in the Journal.

62
00:02:10,319 --> 00:02:12,686
"There is no way
on God's green Earth

63
00:02:12,738 --> 00:02:15,355
"that at least one
of the three name partners

64
00:02:15,407 --> 00:02:17,558
"at Pearson Specter Litt

65
00:02:17,593 --> 00:02:21,445
didn't know what was going on
under their own roof."

66
00:02:21,497 --> 00:02:24,665
"God's green Earth."
Who wrote it?

67
00:02:24,700 --> 00:02:25,999
A partner at Skaaden.

68
00:02:26,035 --> 00:02:27,501
If it wasn't them,
it would've been someone else,

69
00:02:27,536 --> 00:02:29,703
because they smell blood.
I don't care what they smell.

70
00:02:29,755 --> 00:02:31,538
I've given up everything
for this firm,

71
00:02:31,540 --> 00:02:33,290
and if anybody tries
to take it from me,

72
00:02:33,342 --> 00:02:36,376
they'll have to pry it
from my cold, dead hands.

73
00:02:36,378 --> 00:02:38,545
- And what's your goddamn plan?
- Excuse me?

74
00:02:38,597 --> 00:02:40,547
Jessica, our reputation's
taking a beating.

75
00:02:40,599 --> 00:02:41,715
We need to rehabilitate it.

76
00:02:41,767 --> 00:02:43,767
That means pro Bono,
and you know it.

77
00:02:43,802 --> 00:02:46,136
One free case is not going
to move the needle,

78
00:02:46,188 --> 00:02:47,387
no matter how worthy it is.

79
00:02:47,389 --> 00:02:48,722
I'm not talking
about one case.

80
00:02:48,724 --> 00:02:50,390
I'm talking about
a series of cases

81
00:02:50,442 --> 00:02:53,277
for our clients'
most valued charities.

82
00:02:54,980 --> 00:02:57,447
Oh, this better not be
another scheme, Jack.

83
00:02:57,483 --> 00:02:58,782
You think this is a move?

84
00:02:58,817 --> 00:03:00,784
Now why would I ever
think that after you tried

85
00:03:00,819 --> 00:03:04,238
to take my firm from me six
times in the last ten minutes?

86
00:03:04,240 --> 00:03:05,872
I did try
to take over from you.

87
00:03:05,908 --> 00:03:08,625
But I've been at this firm
my entire career,

88
00:03:08,661 --> 00:03:10,210
and I am fighting for it now.

89
00:03:10,246 --> 00:03:11,995
- And you think I'm not?
- I'm sure you are.

90
00:03:12,047 --> 00:03:14,167
But you're also the reason
I'm holding this indictment

91
00:03:14,216 --> 00:03:15,382
of our firm
in the first place,

92
00:03:15,417 --> 00:03:17,134
because what they're
saying is true.

93
00:03:17,169 --> 00:03:18,635
And don't you dare
try to tell me

94
00:03:18,671 --> 00:03:19,886
you didn't know
about Mike Ross,

95
00:03:19,922 --> 00:03:21,755
because we both know you did.

96
00:03:31,016 --> 00:03:32,599
What the hell do you want?

97
00:03:32,601 --> 00:03:34,484
Oh, since you made me come
all the way down here,

98
00:03:34,520 --> 00:03:36,937
I thought I'd save the taxpayers
some money on hiring a server.

99
00:03:36,939 --> 00:03:38,272
A server for what?

100
00:03:38,324 --> 00:03:40,440
For your fiancée. I'd like
to ask her some questions.

101
00:03:40,442 --> 00:03:41,742
Get the hell out of here.

102
00:03:41,777 --> 00:03:43,777
You want to serve a subpoena,
you serve it to her.

103
00:03:43,829 --> 00:03:45,946
Well, then I wouldn't get
to see the look on your face.

104
00:03:45,948 --> 00:03:48,081
Did you really think I wouldn't
hit you where it hurts?

105
00:03:48,117 --> 00:03:50,834
I was saving
your weakest spot for last.

106
00:03:50,869 --> 00:03:52,336
Have a nice day, gentlemen.

107
00:03:56,925 --> 00:03:59,543
- What?
- You know what.

108
00:03:59,595 --> 00:04:01,712
It's time we give that woman
a taste of her own medicine.

109
00:04:01,764 --> 00:04:03,297
What the hell is that
supposed to mean?

110
00:04:03,299 --> 00:04:05,215
It means we hire a lawyer
from an outside firm,

111
00:04:05,267 --> 00:04:07,134
and we dig up dirt on someone
she cares about.

112
00:04:07,186 --> 00:04:09,303
- Are you out of your mind?
- You saw what she did to Donna.

113
00:04:09,355 --> 00:04:11,271
It's only a matter of time
before she tries to pull

114
00:04:11,307 --> 00:04:12,773
the same shit with Rachel.
Mike--

115
00:04:12,808 --> 00:04:14,441
Harvey, you're the one
that taught me that when someone

116
00:04:14,476 --> 00:04:16,193
puts pressure on you,
you put it back on them.

117
00:04:16,228 --> 00:04:18,028
I also taught you if you're
gonna take a swing at someone,

118
00:04:18,063 --> 00:04:20,280
you better knock them out,
and if we pull the shit

119
00:04:20,316 --> 00:04:21,948
that you're talking about
and get caught,

120
00:04:21,984 --> 00:04:24,701
all that happens is
I get thrown off this case,

121
00:04:24,737 --> 00:04:26,703
and it's game over.

122
00:04:26,739 --> 00:04:28,622
Harvey, I can't stand by
and watch while the people

123
00:04:28,657 --> 00:04:30,657
I care about get attacked,
and neither could you.

124
00:04:30,709 --> 00:04:31,992
Mike, I promise you,

125
00:04:32,044 --> 00:04:33,910
I will be there for Rachel
every step of the way.

126
00:04:33,962 --> 00:04:35,295
In the meantime,

127
00:04:35,331 --> 00:04:37,831
I need you going through
every one of those boxes.

128
00:04:37,883 --> 00:04:39,750
Because if that woman
is ready to go to trial,

129
00:04:39,802 --> 00:04:41,501
she's got a lot more
than an e-mail

130
00:04:41,553 --> 00:04:44,104
from Louis' girlfriend.

