00:05:19,865 --> 00:05:21,031
Yes, I know who you are.

145
00:05:21,083 --> 00:05:23,367
I'm flattered you came
for me personally.

146
00:05:23,419 --> 00:05:25,535
But we aren't supposed to talk
for another three days,

147
00:05:25,537 --> 00:05:27,037
and I don't have my lawyer
with me, so--

148
00:05:27,089 --> 00:05:28,839
This isn't
a formal interrogation.

149
00:05:28,874 --> 00:05:30,040
That won't be necessary.

150
00:05:30,092 --> 00:05:32,376
Then I'll tell you
what is necessary.

151
00:05:32,428 --> 00:05:34,211
You're going to put in writing
that anything I say to you

152
00:05:34,213 --> 00:05:35,379
is inadmissible.

153
00:05:35,431 --> 00:05:37,047
I suspected you'd
say that, which is why

154
00:05:37,049 --> 00:05:41,468
I prepared this.

155
00:05:41,520 --> 00:05:44,471
I understand if you'd prefer
to ask somebody who's actually

156
00:05:44,523 --> 00:05:48,392
completed law school
if that's legally binding.

157
00:05:48,444 --> 00:05:50,193
I'm perfectly capable
of determining

158
00:05:50,229 --> 00:05:52,729
if this is legally
binding or not.

159
00:05:52,731 --> 00:05:54,114
and I'm not going to let you

160
00:05:54,149 --> 00:05:56,483
bait me into saying
anything to you.

161
00:05:56,535 --> 00:05:57,567
Well, that's fine with me.

162
00:05:57,569 --> 00:05:59,736
I'm not looking for you to talk.

163
00:05:59,738 --> 00:06:01,488
I'm looking for you to listen.

164
00:06:09,415 --> 00:06:10,414
Well, it's official.

165
00:06:10,416 --> 00:06:11,632
No matter what
happens at trial,

166
00:06:11,667 --> 00:06:13,417
this firm isn't surviving
Mike Ross.

167
00:06:13,419 --> 00:06:15,085
I know about
the editorial, Louis.

168
00:06:15,087 --> 00:06:16,420
What editorial?

169
00:06:16,422 --> 00:06:19,556
I'm talking about the summer
associate applications.

170
00:06:19,591 --> 00:06:20,757
- How bad is it?
- Three people.

171
00:06:20,809 --> 00:06:22,926
Not just any three people,
the three people that never

172
00:06:22,928 --> 00:06:24,811
should've made it to Harvard
in the first place.

173
00:06:24,847 --> 00:06:26,263
Goddamn it.

174
00:06:26,265 --> 00:06:28,315
Sheila's sending us
the bottom of the barrel.

175
00:06:28,350 --> 00:06:30,100
She's giving us
the sludge that grows

176
00:06:30,102 --> 00:06:34,237
at the bottom of the barrel.
Then...

177
00:06:34,273 --> 00:06:38,775
I think it might be time to
start looking beyond Harvard.

178
00:06:38,777 --> 00:06:40,610
Yeah, that's a great idea.
You know what?

179
00:06:40,663 --> 00:06:41,611
We should start shitting
in the urinals

180
00:06:41,613 --> 00:06:42,612
while we're at it.

181
00:06:42,614 --> 00:06:43,697
I'm not talking about

182
00:06:43,749 --> 00:06:45,615
the University
of Arizona, Louis.

183
00:06:45,617 --> 00:06:48,618
I'm talking about Columbia,
Yale, Stanford--

184
00:06:48,620 --> 00:06:51,121
And I'm talking
about appearances.

185
00:06:51,123 --> 00:06:53,590
We break our rule and suddenly
hire outside of Harvard--

186
00:06:53,625 --> 00:06:56,126
We already broke our rule
for Rachel with Columbia.

187
00:06:56,178 --> 00:06:57,961
Please, that was different,
and you know it.

188
00:06:57,963 --> 00:06:59,763
No. It was because of Mike,

189
00:06:59,798 --> 00:07:02,015
which makes it the same
goddamn thing.

190
00:07:02,051 --> 00:07:04,968
One way or another, we are
going to keep this firm going.

191
00:07:04,970 --> 00:07:07,304
So if you don't wanna go
outside of Harvard to do that,

192
00:07:07,356 --> 00:07:10,140
then I suggest you go up
to Cambridge,

193
00:07:10,192 --> 00:07:11,808
and convince Sheila
to start feeding us

194
00:07:11,860 --> 00:07:13,977
some worthy
goddamn applicants.

195
00:07:17,032 --> 00:07:19,566
<i>♪
♪</i>

196
00:07:19,618 --> 00:07:21,702
Okay. So first
you pick me up,

197
00:07:21,737 --> 00:07:23,987
then you bring me
to my favorite café.

198
00:07:24,039 --> 00:07:25,572
What can I say?
I do my homework.

199
00:07:25,624 --> 00:07:27,407
As do I, Ms. Gibbs,
which is why I'm not falling

200
00:07:27,459 --> 00:07:28,825
for you pretending
to be my friend.

201
00:07:28,827 --> 00:07:30,243
You're right.
I'm not your friend.

202
00:07:30,295 --> 00:07:31,661
But I am willing
to pull some strings

203
00:07:31,714 --> 00:07:33,797
to get the man you love
into Columbia Law School.

204
00:07:33,832 --> 00:07:35,999
And if you think that I'm
gonna buy that fairy tale,

205
00:07:36,051 --> 00:07:37,931
the only strings you're trying
to pull are mine.

206
00:07:37,970 --> 00:07:40,003
The only fairy tale here
is the one where you believe

207
00:07:40,055 --> 00:07:42,222
you get out
of this thing unscathed.

208
00:07:42,257 --> 00:07:44,057
Okay.
We're done here.

209
00:07:44,093 --> 00:07:45,675
Rachel, I'm just trying
to give you your options.

210
00:07:45,677 --> 00:07:46,760
I know my options.

211
00:07:46,812 --> 00:07:48,562
Then you know you have
no spousal privilege,

212
00:07:48,597 --> 00:07:50,013
which means you're going to
have to tell the truth,

213
00:07:50,015 --> 00:07:51,481
and put your fiancée away.

214
00:07:51,517 --> 00:07:53,483
Or you're gonna have
to plead the Fifth.

215
00:07:53,519 --> 00:07:55,736
Or I can say that
he didn't do this.

216
00:07:55,771 --> 00:07:57,988
Perjuring yourself is
the same as taking the Fifth,

217
00:07:58,023 --> 00:07:59,406
as far as your future
is concerned.

218
00:07:59,441 --> 00:08:00,690
What the hell
does that mean?

219
00:08:00,692 --> 00:08:02,492
I'm saying that someday
you're going to face

220
00:08:02,528 --> 00:08:04,368
the character and fitness
committee of the Bar,

221
00:08:04,413 --> 00:08:06,079
and I seriously doubt they're
going to admit somebody

222
00:08:06,115 --> 00:08:07,197
who did that.

223
00:08:07,249 --> 00:08:08,448
Are you trying to
intimidate a witness?

224
00:08:08,500 --> 00:08:12,202
Because yes, someday
I will face that committee,

225
00:08:12,204 --> 00:08:14,538
but tomorrow they're going
to be hearing about you.

226
00:08:14,540 --> 00:08:17,124
I'm your only way
out of this mess.

227
00:08:17,176 --> 00:08:20,377
Just give me the people who are
actually responsible for it,

228
00:08:20,429 --> 00:08:23,430
and I'll see to it that both
you and Mike can practice law

229
00:08:23,465 --> 00:08:24,931
for the rest of your lives.

230
00:08:32,808 --> 00:08:34,224
Please tell me
that's the last one.

231
00:08:34,226 --> 00:08:35,609
It is.

232
00:08:35,644 --> 00:08:37,861
Except for the hundred
in the other conference room.

233
00:08:37,896 --> 00:08:39,563
- Holy shit.
- Yeah.

234
00:08:39,565 --> 00:08:41,398
Trial Strategy 101.

235
00:08:41,400 --> 00:08:42,949
Bury the other side
in paperwork,

236
00:08:42,985 --> 00:08:44,785
so they can't find
what they're looking for.

237
00:08:44,820 --> 00:08:46,069
And what are we looking for?

238
00:08:46,071 --> 00:08:47,904
Gibbs' trial strategy.

239
00:08:47,906 --> 00:08:50,624
Somewhere in these boxes
are the pieces

240
