00:08:52,661 --> 00:08:54,077
We find them,
we know specifically

242
00:08:54,079 --> 00:08:55,412
what we have to fight.

243
00:08:55,464 --> 00:08:59,166
And what specifically might
those things look like?

244
00:08:59,218 --> 00:09:02,919
Witness lists, interviews,
anything to do with Lola Jensen,

245
00:09:02,971 --> 00:09:05,138
utility bills from when I was
supposed to be at Harvard--

246
00:09:05,174 --> 00:09:06,923
Wait, wait, wait.
Slow down.

247
00:09:06,975 --> 00:09:09,342
- Why are you writing this down?
- So I can remember it.

248
00:09:09,394 --> 00:09:11,595
And because we need a system.

249
00:09:11,647 --> 00:09:14,097
And because you've never done
doc review before.

250
00:09:15,317 --> 00:09:16,433
I don't believe it.

251
00:09:16,435 --> 00:09:17,934
How you've been a legal
secretary this long,

252
00:09:17,986 --> 00:09:20,070
and never have done doc review.
I will tell you how.

253
00:09:20,105 --> 00:09:22,272
Because I'm the best damn person
you've ever seen

254
00:09:22,274 --> 00:09:24,157
at reading people,
anticipating needs,

255
00:09:24,193 --> 00:09:25,742
and generally
dominating everything.

256
00:09:25,777 --> 00:09:26,860
So, in this situation,

257
00:09:26,912 --> 00:09:28,612
you're going to be
absolutely no help at all.

258
00:09:28,664 --> 00:09:30,447
- None whatsoever.
- I'm getting Rachel.

259
00:09:35,037 --> 00:09:36,503
What's that?

260
00:09:36,538 --> 00:09:37,704
What does it look like?

261
00:09:37,756 --> 00:09:39,556
It looks like something
I don't have time for.

262
00:09:39,591 --> 00:09:40,957
Well, make time.

263
00:09:40,959 --> 00:09:43,677
Jessica, we've got a thousand
boxes of shit to go through,

264
00:09:43,712 --> 00:09:45,879
and I've got trial in two weeks.
What?

265
00:09:45,931 --> 00:09:47,597
That's right.
The date's been set.

266
00:09:47,633 --> 00:09:49,266
So I'm sorry that I can't have
a doughnut with you right now,

267
00:09:49,301 --> 00:09:51,017
but I've got something a little
more important to deal with.

268
00:09:51,053 --> 00:09:53,470
Harvey, I understand, but
our clients are being circled.

269
00:09:53,522 --> 00:09:54,638
Our reputation's getting
tanked,

270
00:09:54,690 --> 00:09:56,556
and we're getting sent
shit associates.

271
00:09:56,608 --> 00:09:57,974
And Mike Ross
is facing prison.

272
00:09:57,976 --> 00:10:00,026
And you're handling
one thing,

273
00:10:00,062 --> 00:10:02,229
while I'm handling
everything else.

274
00:10:02,281 --> 00:10:03,980
- Jessica--
- No, never mind, Harvey.

275
00:10:03,982 --> 00:10:06,816
It's clear that you
really don't care

276
00:10:06,818 --> 00:10:08,285
about keeping
this firm together.

277
00:10:08,320 --> 00:10:09,903
I resigned to keep
this firm together.

278
00:10:09,955 --> 00:10:11,621
Well, it sure doesn't seem
to be working out that way,

279
00:10:11,657 --> 00:10:13,206
does it?

280
00:10:17,296 --> 00:10:20,964
Great, I'll have my secretary
set up a meeting for Monday.

281
00:10:20,999 --> 00:10:23,083
If that meeting's about your
pro Bono bullshit,

282
00:10:23,135 --> 00:10:24,384
cancel it.
What?

283
00:10:24,419 --> 00:10:27,721
You said it yourself, Jack.
Other firms smell blood.

284
00:10:27,756 --> 00:10:30,757
Well, you don't get a shark
to back off by playing nice,

285
00:10:30,809 --> 00:10:33,176
you do it by clubbing him
in the face.

286
00:10:33,228 --> 00:10:35,428
They come after our clients,
we go after theirs.

287
00:10:35,480 --> 00:10:37,314
Clients aren't the ones
writing editorials

288
00:10:37,349 --> 00:10:39,983
for "The Wall Street
Journal", Jack.

289
00:10:40,018 --> 00:10:41,518
You want to poach
an attorney.

290
00:10:41,520 --> 00:10:44,437
I wanna poach
a whole goddamn department.

291
00:10:44,489 --> 00:10:46,156
That is definitely
another way to go.

292
00:10:46,191 --> 00:10:47,691
It's the only way to go,

293
00:10:47,743 --> 00:10:50,110
because if we didn't do what
we're saying we didn't do,

294
00:10:50,162 --> 00:10:51,995
this is what we do.
I get it.

295
00:10:52,030 --> 00:10:54,414
You're trying to convince
the world we're innocent.

296
00:10:54,449 --> 00:10:56,700
Jack, I don't give a shit
if my enemies think

297
00:10:56,752 --> 00:10:58,118
I'm innocent or not.

298
00:10:58,170 --> 00:11:01,454
I give a shit whether they
think they can take me down,

299
00:11:01,506 --> 00:11:02,789
which is why
I'm not going to cower

300
00:11:02,841 --> 00:11:05,208
in some pro Bono corner,
trying to convince them

301
00:11:05,210 --> 00:11:06,626
that I'm friendly.

302
00:11:06,678 --> 00:11:08,962
I'm going to kick some ass,

303
00:11:09,014 --> 00:11:11,798
and remind them
that I'm fierce.

304
00:11:20,392 --> 00:11:22,475
There you are. I've been
looking everywhere for you.

305
00:11:22,527 --> 00:11:25,111
Rachel, we need your help.
Where have you been?

306
00:11:25,147 --> 00:11:26,279
With Anita Gibbs.

307
00:11:26,315 --> 00:11:27,781
What? How did you
let that happen?

308
00:11:27,816 --> 00:11:29,482
Because she ambushed me
on the street,

309
00:11:29,534 --> 00:11:30,900
with a document that said
our conversation

310
00:11:30,953 --> 00:11:32,235
would be inadmissible.

311
00:11:32,287 --> 00:11:33,570
And if she did that
is because she didn't want

312
00:11:33,622 --> 00:11:35,205
to talk to you, she wanted
to get in your head.

313
00:11:35,240 --> 00:11:37,741
Mike, I know what
she wanted to do.

314
00:11:37,793 --> 00:11:39,459
What did she say?

315
00:11:41,797 --> 00:11:44,914
She said that she could
get you into Columbia,

316
00:11:44,916 --> 00:11:47,550
and that you could be a lawyer
after all this is over.

317
00:11:47,586 --> 00:11:48,718
Rachel, she's lying--

318
00:11:48,754 --> 00:11:49,886
You think I don't know that?

319
00:11:49,921 --> 00:11:51,338
Well, we've already
been over this.

320
00:11:51,390 --> 00:11:53,173
The only way she is gonna help
us is if we help her

321
00:11:53,225 --> 00:11:54,507
put Harvey and Jessica away.

322
00:11:54,559 --> 00:11:56,926
Yes, Mike, I know that,
but we didn't go over the part

323
00:11:56,928 --> 00:11:59,429
where I don't get into the Bar
because I took the Fifth.

324
00:11:59,431 --> 00:12:00,597
Oh, goddamn it!

325
00:12:00,649 --> 00:12:02,432
This is exactly why I wanted
Harvey to be there.

326
00:12:02,484 --> 00:12:04,017
She got into your head.
She didn't got into my head.

327
00:12:04,069 --> 00:12:05,735
She dangled our dream
in front of me,

328
00:12:05,771 --> 00:12:07,937
and I know
that we can't have that.

329
00:12:07,990 --> 00:12:09,739
It doesn't mean
I can't handle this.

330
00:12:13,111 --> 00:12:14,744
It doesn't seem
like you're handling it.

331
00:12:14,780 --> 00:12:16,112
- I am.
- You're crying.

332
00:12:16,164 --> 00:12:18,782
No. I'm releasing my emotions
so that I can persevere

333
00:12:18,834 --> 00:12:22,202
instead of denying them
and losing my mind.

334
00:12:22,254 --> 00:12:23,870
Which I can't do today,

335
00:12:23,922 --> 00:12:25,622
because I have a meeting
with the dean.

336
00:12:25,674 --> 00:12:27,540
Now, I came in here
to be alone

337
00:12:27,592 --> 00:12:28,792
so I can deal with my shit,

338
00:12:28,844 --> 00:12:31,344
so if you don't mind,
I would like to be alone

339
00:12:31,380 --> 00:12:32,679
so I can deal with my shit.

340
00:12:45,042 --> 00:12:46,882
Hey, did you find something
in the discovery?

341
00:12:46,911 --> 00:12:47,994
Yeah, sure as hell did.

342
00:12:48,046 --> 00:12:50,413
I just discovered that Gibbs
picked up Rachel.

343
00:12:50,415 --> 00:12:51,580
What?
She arrested her?

344
00:12:51,633 --> 00:12:53,553
No, she pulled up to the curb
with some document.

345
00:12:53,584 --> 00:12:55,251
I don't give a shit what she
pulled up with.

346
00:12:55,253 --> 00:12:56,502
Rachel should know
not to go with her.

347
00:12:56,554 --> 00:12:58,004
Yeah, and that would've been
an excellent thing

348
00:12:58,056 --> 00:13:00,306
for her lawyer to tell her,
except her lawyer wasn't there.

349
00:13:00,341 --> 00:13:01,590
- Excuse me?
- You promised me

350
00:13:01,592 --> 00:13:03,426
that you would be with her
every step of the way.

351
00:13:03,428 --> 00:13:05,428
I promised I'd represent her
at a deposition,

352
00:13:05,480 --> 00:13:07,146
not babysit her
24 hours a day.

353
00:13:07,181 --> 00:13:09,598
Maybe instead of getting mad
at Rachel, it is time for us

354
00:13:09,600 --> 00:13:11,350
to figure out
how to go after Gibbs.

355
00:13:11,402 --> 00:13:12,935
- This again.
- Yes, this again.

356
00:13:12,937 --> 00:13:15,271
I told you she was gonna go
after Rachel, and now she has.

357
00:13:15,273 --> 00:13:17,156
And I told you if you're
gonna go after someone,

358
00:13:17,191 --> 00:13:18,441
you better knock them out.

359
00:13:18,493 --> 00:13:20,660
Then you better figure out
a way to knock Gibbs out soon,

360
00:13:20,695 --> 00:13:23,079
because if you don't, I will.

361
00:13:32,123 --> 00:13:35,458
Louis.

362
00:13:35,460 --> 00:13:37,376
What are you doing here?
What?

363
00:13:37,428 --> 00:13:39,061
You thought you could lie to
my face and get away with it?

364
00:13:39,097 --> 00:13:40,379
- I never lied to you.
- Really?

365
00:13:40,431 --> 00:13:41,764
Because you swore
you wouldn't come forward

366
00:13:41,799 --> 00:13:43,215
about that e-mail,
but you did.

367
00:13:43,267 --> 00:13:45,101
And you you're pulling
this associate shit.

368
00:13:45,136 --> 00:13:46,802
I didn't come forward.
They found me.

369
00:13:46,804 --> 00:13:48,437
And I'm not pulling
any associate shit.

370
00:13:48,473 --> 00:13:49,889
Then what do you call
this pathetic excuse

371
00:13:49,941 --> 00:13:51,640
of a candidates list?
I call it inevitable.

372
00:13:51,693 --> 00:13:53,809
Because our students can read.

373
00:13:53,861 --> 00:13:55,144
- The editorial.
- Yes.

374
00:13:55,146 --> 00:13:57,146
The editorial.

375
00:13:58,399 --> 00:14:00,066
So you're not
sending us sludge.

376
00:14:00,118 --> 00:14:02,318
Louis, I'm not
doing anything.

377
00:14:02,370 --> 00:14:06,489
Your firm is being investigated
by the U.S. Attorney's office.

378
00:14:06,491 --> 00:14:09,241
And no one is going to risk
their career on a place

379
00:14:09,293 --> 00:14:11,210
that may not even exist
in a month.

380
00:14:11,245 --> 00:14:14,463
They might,
if you convince them to.

381
00:14:14,499 --> 00:14:17,083
- Louis, I can't do that.
- Sheila, please.

382
00:14:17,135 --> 00:14:19,135
I came here once before,
hoping for a second chance

383
00:14:19,170 --> 00:14:20,336
and you wouldn't
give it to me.

384
00:14:20,338 --> 00:14:21,670
What does that
have to do with this?

385
00:14:21,672 --> 00:14:23,055
Because if we'd gotten
back together then,

386
00:14:23,091 --> 00:14:24,473
I wouldn't even be
at the firm now,

387
00:14:24,509 --> 00:14:26,175
but I am.

388
00:14:26,227 --> 00:14:28,511
And it's all I have.

389
00:14:28,563 --> 00:14:32,098
I understand you not giving
me a second chance then.

390
00:14:33,601 --> 00:14:37,069
But I'm begging you...

391
00:14:37,105 --> 00:14:38,988
give my firm one now.

392
00:14:39,023 --> 00:14:43,609
Louis, even if I wanted to,
it won't work.

393
00:14:43,661 --> 00:14:45,694
- You don't know that.
- Yes, I do.

394
00:14:45,696 --> 00:14:48,030
Because they're going to ask me
if I think it's a good idea

395
00:14:48,082 --> 00:14:51,333
for them to work at Pearson
Specter Litt, and I don't.

396
00:14:51,369 --> 00:14:54,503
- Sheila--
- Louis.

397
00:14:54,539 --> 00:14:56,756
Please don't ask me
to lie to them.

398
00:15:03,765 --> 00:15:05,181
What are you doing?

399
00:15:05,216 --> 00:15:06,849
I'm just wondering
if you're gonna stay in here

400
00:15:06,884 --> 00:15:08,050
going over stuff all day.

401
00:15:08,102 --> 00:15:09,969
What else would I be doing?
Going to the ball game?

402
00:15:10,021 --> 00:15:11,554
I don't know, Harvey,

403
00:15:11,556 --> 00:15:13,189
I thought maybe you'd be doing
something to get Anita Gibbs

404
00:15:13,224 --> 00:15:14,273
to back off Rachel.

405
00:15:14,308 --> 00:15:16,058
Donna, she threatened
to go to the Bar.

406
00:15:16,060 --> 00:15:18,060
It's a bullshit hypothetical
that she couldn't do

407
00:15:18,062 --> 00:15:19,445
until after Rachel testified.

408
00:15:19,480 --> 00:15:21,063
Which is after
the trial starts,

409
00:15:21,115 --> 00:15:22,648
and that's what I'm
goddamn working on.

410
00:15:22,700 --> 00:15:24,533
Harvey, all I'm saying is

411
00:15:24,569 --> 00:15:26,902
that when Mike gets worked up
about something,

412
00:15:26,904 --> 00:15:28,584
he doesn't tend to make
the best decisions.

413
00:15:28,623 --> 00:15:30,039
Well, if he doesn't work
on the discovery,

414
00:15:30,074 --> 00:15:32,491
he's gonna go to jail, so...

415
00:15:32,543 --> 00:15:34,677
what do you want me to do?
I don't know, Harvey.

416
00:15:34,712 --> 00:15:36,629
But you better at least
go talk to Anita Gibbs,

417
00:15:36,664 --> 00:15:38,664
because Mike gave you
a warning loud and clear.

418
00:15:38,716 --> 00:15:41,250
If you don't do something,
he will.

419
00:15:51,179 --> 00:15:54,096
Jack, I don't often come
outside for my coffee,

420
00:15:54,098 --> 00:15:56,432
but when I do is because
I'm feeling the need

421
00:15:56,434 --> 00:15:57,817
for a little alone time.

422
00:15:57,852 --> 00:16:00,269
Well, I came out here because
I knew you wouldn't want

423
00:16:00,271 --> 00:16:03,405
anyone hearing
what I have to say.

424
00:16:03,441 --> 00:16:05,741
Are you here to tell me
you can get the job done?

425
00:16:05,776 --> 00:16:08,444
No, I'm here to tell you
if you want me to get it done,

426
00:16:08,446 --> 00:16:10,830
you're going to have
to open your wallet.

427
00:16:10,865 --> 00:16:12,615
I'm not paying you
more money,

428
00:16:12,667 --> 00:16:14,200
just to get you to
poach a department.

429
00:16:14,252 --> 00:16:15,701
I'm not talking about me.

430
00:16:15,753 --> 00:16:18,871
I'm talking the real estate
division of Baker Hostetler.

431
00:16:18,923 --> 00:16:21,173
- How much do they want?
- Double what they're making.

432
00:16:21,209 --> 00:16:24,793
Are you insane? That's what
broke Dewey Ballantine.

433
00:16:24,846 --> 00:16:26,679
You can't have two classes
of partners.

434
00:16:26,714 --> 00:16:28,264
Then we can't poach
a department,

435
00:16:28,299 --> 00:16:30,466
because they're the only ones
even willing to come here,

436
00:16:30,468 --> 00:16:32,434
considering what's going on.

437
00:16:35,473 --> 00:16:37,640
Then make the offer.

438
00:16:37,642 --> 00:16:40,976
And let me have
my goddamn coffee in peace.

439
00:16:48,402 --> 00:16:49,485
Ms. Scott,

440
00:16:49,537 --> 00:16:51,120
there's a Harvey Specter
here to see you.

441
00:16:51,155 --> 00:16:53,239
He says it's urgent.

442
00:16:53,291 --> 00:16:54,406
Send him in.

443
00:16:55,793 --> 00:16:57,760
I don't believe it.

444
00:16:57,795 --> 00:17:00,429
You have some balls pretending
to be Harvey to get in here.

445
00:17:00,464 --> 00:17:02,198
Well, you did call me
"Baby Harvey" once.

446
00:17:02,233 --> 00:17:03,732
I don't give a shit
what I called you.

447
00:17:03,768 --> 00:17:05,384
Get out! Now!
Scottie, Scottie, please.

448
00:17:05,419 --> 00:17:07,336
Listen, I knew you would
never agree to see me,

449
00:17:07,388 --> 00:17:08,387
and I need to talk to you.

450
00:17:08,422 --> 00:17:10,556
About what?

451
00:17:10,591 --> 00:17:12,007
I need someone
to bring an action

452
00:17:12,009 --> 00:17:14,093
against Anita Gibbs' sister.
Are you insane?

453
00:17:14,145 --> 00:17:16,011
Listen to me.
She's not just coming after me.

454
00:17:16,013 --> 00:17:18,814
She's coming after my fiancée.
I don't care.

455
00:17:18,849 --> 00:17:20,733
If I do that, I might as well
call the woman up,

456
00:17:20,768 --> 00:17:22,735
and tell her that I'm in
on your whole bullshit too.

457
00:17:22,770 --> 00:17:24,019
We get someone
from your firm--

458
00:17:24,071 --> 00:17:25,654
Not to mention I told Harvey
that I never

459
00:17:25,690 --> 00:17:28,190
even wanted to hear
your name again.

460
00:17:29,410 --> 00:17:31,193
He didn't tell you
about that, did he?

461
00:17:32,530 --> 00:17:33,946
Well, I guess
he hasn't changed,

462
00:17:33,998 --> 00:17:35,364
because he didn't
tell me about you

463
00:17:35,366 --> 00:17:37,032
until it was too late either.

464
00:17:37,084 --> 00:17:39,785
So I am sorry
about your fiancée,

465
00:17:39,837 --> 00:17:41,370
but I need you to go now.

466
00:17:41,422 --> 00:17:42,955
Scottie, this woman
is not gonna stop

467
00:17:43,007 --> 00:17:44,540
until she gets
what she wants.

468
00:17:44,542 --> 00:17:46,675
And what she wants
is Harvey.

469
00:17:46,711 --> 00:17:49,378
So I'm not asking you to do
this for me and Rachel.

470
00:17:49,380 --> 00:17:51,013
I'm asking you
to do it for him.

471
00:18:03,527 --> 00:18:05,227
Is that an invitation
to your <i>bar mitzvah?</i>

472
00:18:05,229 --> 00:18:06,528
because I'm busy that day.

473
00:18:06,564 --> 00:18:08,030
It's a motion
to have you sanctioned

474
00:18:08,065 --> 00:18:09,698
for improperly
contacting a witness.

475
00:18:09,734 --> 00:18:11,400
I didn't improperly
contact anyone.

476
00:18:11,402 --> 00:18:12,735
Oh, bullshit.

477
00:18:12,737 --> 00:18:14,203
You got Rachel Zane alone
so you could offer her

478
00:18:14,238 --> 00:18:15,404
a deal to turn on me.

479
00:18:15,456 --> 00:18:16,956
And there's nothing wrong
with that.

480
00:18:16,991 --> 00:18:17,991
You listen to me.

481
00:18:18,042 --> 00:18:19,408
You've been pulling shit
like this

482
00:18:19,410 --> 00:18:21,160
from the second
this thing started.

483
00:18:21,212 --> 00:18:23,212
You denied my client access
to his attorney,

484
00:18:23,247 --> 00:18:25,047
you fabricated charges
against Donna,

485
00:18:25,082 --> 00:18:26,642
and now you're tampering
with a witness.

486
00:18:26,667 --> 00:18:29,084
