560
00:21:22,088 --> 00:21:23,637
I didn't chose him over you.

561
00:21:23,672 --> 00:21:25,172
Yes, you did.

562
00:21:25,174 --> 00:21:26,390
And whether you choose
to admit it or not,

563
00:21:26,425 --> 00:21:27,391
it was Mike's secret

564
00:21:27,426 --> 00:21:29,093
that broke us up
in the first place.

565
00:21:41,907 --> 00:21:43,440
You let her in here
without telling me?

566
00:21:43,492 --> 00:21:44,942
I was in the conference room,
going over discovery.

567
00:21:44,994 --> 00:21:46,610
What are you going to do?

568
00:21:46,662 --> 00:21:47,995
I don't know what I'm gonna
do, but whatever it is,

569
00:21:48,030 --> 00:21:49,663
I'm gonna do it right now.
Harvey, calm down.

570
00:21:49,698 --> 00:21:51,865
I'm not gonna calm down,
you told me to go after Gibbs

571
00:21:51,917 --> 00:21:53,667
to stop Mike from doing
something stupid,

572
00:21:53,702 --> 00:21:55,836
and I did, and all that did
was waste our time

573
00:21:55,871 --> 00:21:57,204
like I said it would.
Harvey.

574
00:21:57,256 --> 00:22:00,090
Gibbs is attacking Rachel,
the woman he loves.

575
00:22:00,126 --> 00:22:02,126
You of all people should be
able to understand that.

576
00:22:02,178 --> 00:22:03,343
I don't give a shit.

577
00:22:03,379 --> 00:22:05,629
He had no right to go after
someone I love.

578
00:22:06,715 --> 00:22:08,215
Okay, you know what, Harvey?

579
00:22:08,267 --> 00:22:10,717
Mike is the one on trial here,
not Scottie.

580
00:22:10,719 --> 00:22:12,386
And all he did was ask her
to do something.

581
00:22:12,388 --> 00:22:14,438
So maybe the thing that you're
really upset about

582
00:22:14,473 --> 00:22:15,722
is that she was right.

583
00:22:22,448 --> 00:22:24,314
Well, how did it go?

584
00:22:24,366 --> 00:22:27,234
We've known
each other a long time, Jack,

585
00:22:27,236 --> 00:22:30,737
and I'd really like to help,
but it's not gonna happen.

586
00:22:30,739 --> 00:22:32,739
You said if I could
get them double--

587
00:22:32,741 --> 00:22:35,659
I said it would take at least
double just to get me to ask.

588
00:22:35,711 --> 00:22:37,377
I did, and they laughed me
out of the room.

589
00:22:37,413 --> 00:22:38,912
What if I could
get you more?

590
00:22:38,914 --> 00:22:40,464
There's no number that's
going to get them to come

591
00:22:40,499 --> 00:22:42,466
to Pearson Specter because they
don't believe there's gonna be

592
00:22:42,501 --> 00:22:43,501
a firm to come to.

593
00:22:43,552 --> 00:22:46,086
Then why did you ask
to meet me here?

594
00:22:46,088 --> 00:22:48,505
Because after I asked them
about your offer,

595
00:22:48,557 --> 00:22:50,174
I asked them about mine.

596
00:22:51,260 --> 00:22:52,426
What are you talking about?

597
00:22:52,428 --> 00:22:54,344
I told them a former
fraternity brother of mine,

598
00:22:54,396 --> 00:22:55,896
who happens to be
a kick-ass lawyer

599
00:22:55,931 --> 00:22:58,265
might be looking for a change.

600
00:22:58,317 --> 00:22:59,850
You're offering me a job?

601
00:22:59,902 --> 00:23:02,436
Jack, Pearson Specter's
a sinking ship.

602
00:23:02,438 --> 00:23:03,770
We've taken on some water.

603
00:23:03,772 --> 00:23:05,689
You've taken on an ocean.

604
00:23:05,741 --> 00:23:07,441
Why the hell would
you wanna stay there?

605
00:23:07,493 --> 00:23:08,942
I'll tell you why.

606
00:23:08,994 --> 00:23:11,828
Because if that ship sinks,
I'll find myself another job.

607
00:23:11,864 --> 00:23:12,946
But if it doesn't,

608
00:23:12,998 --> 00:23:14,615
I have the chance to be one
of the captains.

609
00:23:14,667 --> 00:23:17,918
If I come to you now, I'll
never be more than a lifer.

610
00:23:17,953 --> 00:23:21,121
As my friend,
tell me I'm wrong.

611
00:23:22,958 --> 00:23:24,958
You're not wrong.

612
00:23:30,799 --> 00:23:38,805
<i>♪
♪</i>

613
00:23:39,892 --> 00:23:41,475
Don't tell me they printed out

614
00:23:41,477 --> 00:23:43,777
a special evening edition
on us too.

615
00:23:43,812 --> 00:23:45,229
Not yet.

616
00:23:45,281 --> 00:23:50,651
I read it, by the way,
on the flight up to Boston.

617
00:23:53,072 --> 00:23:55,072
And did it fire you up?

618
00:23:57,576 --> 00:23:59,243
Pissed me the hell off.

619
00:24:04,333 --> 00:24:06,333
You couldn't get it done
with Sheila, could you?

620
00:24:06,385 --> 00:24:11,004
Jessica, she didn't send us
the candidates on that list.

621
00:24:11,056 --> 00:24:14,091
They were the only three that
even asked to be submitted,

622
00:24:14,143 --> 00:24:16,677
and it was because
of bullshit like that.

